This paper deals with the problem of detecting errors in electronic dictionaries stored in XML format. The methods described in the paper involve statistical anomaly detection techniques, which are commonly used in natural language processing and information retrieval (cs.CL, cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of language models and tied-field models, which are techniques commonly used in database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for detecting errors, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
